main event: Multiple unidentified flying objects were reported in the Galesburg and Moline areas of Illinois between March 6 and March 9, 1967.
interesting points: Sightings were reported by several witnesses including police officers, a traffic policeman, and local residents., The objects were described as metallic, disc-shaped, and moving at high rates of speed., Some witnesses claimed to observe glowing or flashing lights and noticed unusual flight patterns, including sharp turns and hovering behaviors., A Moline policeman filmed what he described as a 'boxcar-shaped' object, contributing to the media coverage of the sightings., Physical evidence such as plastic bags and kites were later investigated, leading some to attribute sightings to weather balloons or other explainable phenomena.
witness description: witnesses included police officers, traffic policemen, and local residents, with varying accounts of shapes and movements of the objects.
